#
# UNICORE/X configuration files
#

startup.properties (used only on Unix):

  This file is imported by the start/stop scripts. 
  It contains basic settings such as Java command, 
  lib, conf and log directories, location of PID file.

logging.properties

  Configures the logging subsystem (Log4j)

uas.config

  This is the basic UNICORE/X configuration file.
  Other config files are referenced from here.

container.properties

  This file contains service definitions and property 
  settings. It also contains the settings for the 
  persistence subsystem.

xnjs.properties

  This file contains the settings for connecting to the TSI.

simpleidb

  Contains application definitions, resource limits, execution 
  environments, etc. Referenced from xnjs.properties

simpleuudb (optional)

  Map file for mapping distinguished names to role, xlogin and other 
  attributes. May be used as alternative or in addition to UVOS or XUUDB.

rest-users.txt (optional)

  Usernames/passwords for authenticating users via the REST API.

xacml2.config

  Configures the XACML2.0 subsystem.

xacml2Policies

  Directory containing XACML2.0 access control policy files.

vo.config (optional, used with UVOS)

  Configuration for interfacing to the VO system.

wrapper.conf (used only on Windows)

  Basic settings for starting UNICORE/X on Windows.


